<subSubSection id="C34D90CEF516FFF5FF8FF99AFA4BFD31" lastPageId="16" lastPageNumber="681" pageId="15" pageNumber="680" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BE8C345F516FFEAFF8FF99AFDDAF811" blockId="15.[113,752,1598,2038]" pageId="15" pageNumber="680">
<emphasis id="B9231F57F516FFEAFF8FF99AFF1BF9B1" bold="true" box="[113,230,1598,1622]" pageId="15" pageNumber="680">
<emphasis id="B9231F57F516FFEAFF8FF99AFF22F9B1" bold="true" box="[113,223,1598,1622]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="680">Diagnosis</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
— This the smallest species in the genus, with a body length of 
<quantity id="4CAF6EA0F516FFEAFECCF9FAFE2EF991" box="[306,467,1630,1654]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.36" metricValueMax="1.44" metricValueMin="1.28" pageId="15" pageNumber="680" unit="mm" value="13.6" valueMax="14.4" valueMin="12.8">12.8–14.4 mm</quantity>
. The dorsomedial process of the male genital capsule is broadly triangular (
<figureCitation id="136CDFC0F516FFEAFD6FF9DAFD1FF971" box="[657,738,1662,1686]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="16.[138,182,1976,1998]" captionTargetBox="[159,1460,1145,1971]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="Figs. 37–39. Gestroiella siamensis D. Polhemus, J. Polhemus &amp; Sites, structural details, specimen from Thailand, Thailand, Songkla Prov., Ton Nga Chang. 37. Female terminal abdomen, ventral view, showing shape of subgenital plate. 38. Male left paramere. 39. Medial process of male phallotheca." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5352730" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5352730/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="680">Fig. 39</figureCitation>
), and the lateral spines of abdominal segments III and IV are relatively small. In males, the posterior margin of abdominal sternum VI is distinctly convex in the middle, and the opposable surfaces of the profemur and tibia are evenly arcuate, rather than having an anteriorly bowed profemur with a gap between it and the protibia as in other members of the genus. The male phallotheca is abruptly narrowed beyond the tips of the parameres, the parameres themselves are relatively slender (
<figureCitation id="136CDFC0F516FFEAFE96F83AFE47F851" box="[360,442,1950,1974]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="16.[138,182,1976,1998]" captionTargetBox="[159,1460,1145,1971]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="Figs. 37–39. Gestroiella siamensis D. Polhemus, J. Polhemus &amp; Sites, structural details, specimen from Thailand, Thailand, Songkla Prov., Ton Nga Chang. 37. Female terminal abdomen, ventral view, showing shape of subgenital plate. 38. Male left paramere. 39. Medial process of male phallotheca." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5352730" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5352730/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="680">Fig. 38</figureCitation>
), and a mat of dark hairs is present on the phallobase. The female subgenital plate is weakly notched apicomedially (
<figureCitation id="136CDFC0F516FFEAFE34F87AFDE6F811" box="[458,539,2014,2038]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="16.[138,182,1976,1998]" captionTargetBox="[159,1460,1145,1971]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="Figs. 37–39. Gestroiella siamensis D. Polhemus, J. Polhemus &amp; Sites, structural details, specimen from Thailand, Thailand, Songkla Prov., Ton Nga Chang. 37. Female terminal abdomen, ventral view, showing shape of subgenital plate. 38. Male left paramere. 39. Medial process of male phallotheca." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5352730" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5352730/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="680">Fig. 37</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF2893CDF516FFEAFCD2F855FB62F7A6" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5352728" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5352728" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5352728/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="680" startId="15.[812,847,2033,2055]" targetBox="[823,1442,1288,2000]" targetPageId="15">
<paragraph id="8BE8C345F516FFEAFCD2F855FB62F7A6" blockId="15.[812,1452,2033,2113]" pageId="15" pageNumber="680">
Fig. 36. 
<taxonomicName id="4C57B8C6F516FFEAFC80F856FA55F7E0" authority="D. Polhemus, J. Polhemus &amp; Sites" authorityName=", D. Polhemus, J. Polhemus &amp; Sites" authorityYear="2008" box="[894,1448,2033,2055]" class="Insecta" family="Naucoridae" genus="Gestroiella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="680" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="siamensis">
<emphasis id="B9231F57F516FFEAFC80F856FBB3F7E1" box="[894,1102,2034,2054]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="680">Gestroiella siamensis</emphasis>
D. Polhemus, J. Polhemus &amp; Sites
</taxonomicName>
, male, dorsal habitus, specimen from Thailand, Songkla Prov., Ton Nga Chang (Young Sohn illustration).
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8BE8C345F509FFF5FF76FF1BFD0CFDB1" blockId="16.[136,776,190,598]" pageId="16" pageNumber="681">
onto the metasternum, with segment III very elongated; the tarsi, which are 3-segmented, with the fore tarsi articulated and not fused to fore femur as in 
<taxonomicName id="4C57B8C6F509FFF5FE0EFF5AFD93FEF1" baseAuthorityName="Stys &amp; Jansson" baseAuthorityYear="1988" box="[496,622,254,278]" class="Insecta" family="Naucoridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="681" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Naucoridae</taxonomicName>
; the persistent dorsal abdominal scent glands in adults; and the abdominal spiracles, which are surrounded by rosettes, this latter character diagnostic for the family. The combination of a long rostrum, long antennae, and abdominal spiracular rosettes is distinctive unique within the 
<taxonomicName id="4C57B8C6F509FFF5FE16FE3AFD8EFE51" box="[488,627,414,438]" class="Insecta" infraOrder="Nepomorpha" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="685" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="infraOrder">Nepomorpha</taxonomicName>
(see 
<figureCitation id="136CDFC0F509FFF5FD4CFE3AFCFEFE51" box="[690,771,414,438]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="16.[836,875,2006,2028]" captionText="Fig. 40. Aphelocheirus (Aphelocheirus) pallens Horváth, macropterous male, dorsal habitus, specimen from Papua New Guinea, Gulf Prov., Sapoi River nr. Lakekamu, CL 7146 (Young Sohn illustration)." pageId="16" pageNumber="681">Fig. 40</figureCitation>
, depicting the macropterous form of 
<taxonomicName id="4C57B8C6F509FFF5FDF8FE1BFD30FE31" authority="Horvath" authorityName="Horvath" authorityYear="1899" box="[518,717,446,470]" class="Insecta" family="Aphelocheiridae" genus="Aphelocheirus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="681" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pallens">
<emphasis id="B9231F57F509FFF5FDF8FE1BFD8DFE31" box="[518,624,447,470]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="681">A. pallens</emphasis>
Horváth
</taxonomicName>
from New 
<collectingCountry id="F34083D5F509FFF5FF41FE7AFEF6FE11" box="[191,267,478,502]" name="Guinea-Bissau" pageId="16" pageNumber="681">Guinea</collectingCountry>
as an exemplar of this family). Useful characters for separating individual species include the male genitalia (
<figureCitation id="136CDFC0F509FFF5FF6EFDBAFF17FDD1" box="[144,234,542,566]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="17.[113,157,1948,1970]" captionTargetBox="[109,757,1020,1917]" captionTargetId="figure-458@17.[97,769,1010,1932]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="Figs.41–46.Aphelocheirus (Aphelocheirus) femoratus D. Polhemus &amp; J. Polhemus, structural details, specimens from Malaysia, Pahang, Cameron Highlands. 41. Brachypterous male, dorsal habitus. 42. Macropterous male, dorsal habitus. 43. Male parameres and phallotheca. 44. Female subgenital plate. 45. Male hind femur, ventral view. 46. Proacetabula." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5352732" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5352732/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="681">Figs. 43</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="136CDFC0F509FFF5FF08FDBAFEEEFDD1" box="[246,275,542,566]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="18.[137,181,1918,1940]" captionTargetBox="[136,776,862,1891]" captionTargetId="figure-371@18.[118,795,850,1903]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="Figs. 47–52.Aphelocheirus (Aphelocheirus) grik D. Polhemus &amp; J. Polhemus, structural details. 47. Brachypterous male, dorsal habitus, Malaysia, Perak, Grik. 48. Macropterous female, dorsal habitus, specimen from Thailand, Chiang Mai Prov.. Mae Ping River. 49. Male ventral abdomen, showing tab on abdominal ventrite IV. 50. Female subgenital plate. 51. Male parameres and phallotheca. 52. Proacetabula." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5352734" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5352734/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="681">51</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="136CDFC0F509FFF5FEE0FDBAFEC6FDD1" box="[286,315,542,566]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="18.[836,879,1948,1970]" captionTargetBox="[834,1477,1158,1911]" captionTargetId="figure-430@18.[811,1503,1147,1916]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="Figs.53–57.Aphelocheirus (Aphelocheirus) malayanus D.Polhemus &amp; J. Polhemus, structural details. 53. Brachypterous male, dorsal habitus, specimen from Malaysia, Perak, near Jeli. 54. Macropterous female, dorsal habitus, specimen from Malaysia, Pahang, Cameron Highlands. 55. Male parameres and phallotheca. 56. Proacetabula. 57. Female subgenital plate." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5352736" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5352736/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="681">55</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="136CDFC0F509FFF5FEB9FDBAFE73FDD1" box="[327,398,542,566]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="19.[113,157,2035,2057]" captionTargetBox="[114,754,1544,2002]" captionTargetId="figure-758@19.[97,772,1516,2015]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="Figs. 58, 59. Aphelocheirus (Micraphelocheirus) malayensis Zettel &amp; Papáček, male parameres. 58. Left paramere. 59. Right paramere (after Zettel &amp; Papáček 2006)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5352738" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5352738/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="681">58, 59</figureCitation>
), female subgenital plate (
<figureCitation id="136CDFC0F509FFF5FD57FDBAFCFEFDD1" box="[681,771,542,566]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="17.[113,157,1948,1970]" captionTargetBox="[109,757,1020,1917]" captionTargetId="figure-458@17.[97,769,1010,1932]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="Figs.41–46.Aphelocheirus (Aphelocheirus) femoratus D. Polhemus &amp; J. Polhemus, structural details, specimens from Malaysia, Pahang, Cameron Highlands. 41. Brachypterous male, dorsal habitus. 42. Macropterous male, dorsal habitus. 43. Male parameres and phallotheca. 44. Female subgenital plate. 45. Male hind femur, ventral view. 46. Proacetabula." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5352732" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5352732/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="681">Figs. 44</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="136CDFC0F509FFF5FF76FD9AFF58FDB1" box="[136,165,574,598]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="18.[137,181,1918,1940]" captionTargetBox="[136,776,862,1891]" captionTargetId="figure-371@18.[118,795,850,1903]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="Figs. 47–52.Aphelocheirus (Aphelocheirus) grik D. Polhemus &amp; J. Polhemus, structural details. 47. Brachypterous male, dorsal habitus, Malaysia, Perak, Grik. 48. Macropterous female, dorsal habitus, specimen from Thailand, Chiang Mai Prov.. Mae Ping River. 49. Male ventral abdomen, showing tab on abdominal ventrite IV. 50. Female subgenital plate. 51. Male parameres and phallotheca. 52. Proacetabula." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5352734" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5352734/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="681">50</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="136CDFC0F509FFF5FF4FFD9AFF33FDB1" box="[177,206,574,598]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="18.[836,879,1948,1970]" captionTargetBox="[834,1477,1158,1911]" captionTargetId="figure-430@18.[811,1503,1147,1916]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="Figs.53–57.Aphelocheirus (Aphelocheirus) malayanus D.Polhemus &amp; J. Polhemus, structural details. 53. Brachypterous male, dorsal habitus, specimen from Malaysia, Perak, near Jeli. 54. Macropterous female, dorsal habitus, specimen from Malaysia, Pahang, Cameron Highlands. 55. Male parameres and phallotheca. 56. Proacetabula. 57. Female subgenital plate." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5352736" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5352736/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="681">57</figureCitation>
), and shape of the proacetabula (
