<paragraph id="8BE8C345F509FFF5FF76FDDBFA3EFF31" blockId="16.[136,777,638,1079]" lastBlockId="16.[836,1475,190,214]" pageId="16" pageNumber="681">
<taxonomicName id="4C57B8C6F509FFF5FF76FDDBFE77FD71" box="[136,394,638,662]" class="Insecta" family="Aphelocheiridae" genus="Aphelocheirus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="681" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="B9231F57F509FFF5FF76FDDBFED1FD71" box="[136,300,639,662]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="681">Aphelocheirus</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
are inhabitants of rocky upland streams, where their use of plastron respiration, associated with the development of the spiracular rosettes, allows them to stay submerged underwater for an indefinite period of time. Individuals are most abundant in areas of mixed gravel and cobble substrate swept by moderate current (D. Polhemus &amp; J. Polhemus, 1989). Such habitats are generally absent in 
<collectingCountry id="F34083D5F509FFF5FF76FCFAFF0AFC91" box="[136,247,862,886]" name="Singapore" pageId="16" pageNumber="681">Singapore</collectingCountry>
, but are by contrast extensive in the mountains of Peninsular 
<collectingCountry id="F34083D5F509FFF5FF02FCDAFEA2FC71" box="[252,351,894,918]" name="Malaysia" pageId="16" pageNumber="681">Malaysia</collectingCountry>
, where representatives of both subgenera currently recognised in the genus, 
<taxonomicName id="4C57B8C6F509FFF5FDD2FC3BFD2EFC51" authorityName="Westwood" authorityYear="1833" box="[556,723,927,950]" class="Insecta" family="Aphelocheiridae" genus="Aphelocheirus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="681" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9231F57F509FFF5FDD2FC3BFD2EFC51" box="[556,723,927,950]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="681">Aphelocheirus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C57B8C6F509FFF5FF76FC1BFEAEFC31" authorityName="Hoberlandt &amp; Stys" authorityYear="1979" box="[136,339,959,982]" class="Insecta" family="Aphelocheiridae" genus="Aphelocheirus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="684" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Micraphelocheirus">
<emphasis id="B9231F57F509FFF5FF76FC1BFEAEFC31" box="[136,339,959,982]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="681">Micraphelocheirus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, are known to occur, and it is likely that the current aphelocheirid fauna of this area is underestimated. No species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C57B8C6F509FFF5FED2FC5BFE35FBF1" authorityName="Westwood" authorityYear="1833" box="[300,456,1023,1046]" class="Insecta" family="Aphelocheiridae" genus="Aphelocheirus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="681" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9231F57F509FFF5FED2FC5BFE35FBF1" box="[300,456,1023,1046]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="681">Aphelocheirus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has yet been recorded from 
<collectingCountry id="F34083D5F509FFF5FF76FBBAFF0AFBD1" box="[136,247,1054,1078]" name="Singapore" pageId="16" pageNumber="681">Singapore</collectingCountry>
, and the genus is unlikely to occur there given the general absence of suitable rocky streams on the island.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE8C345F509FFF5FCBAFF5AFA4BFD31" blockId="16.[836,1474,254,726]" pageId="16" pageNumber="681">
Following the monograph of D. Polhemus &amp; J. Polhemus (1989), which established a firm taxonomic foundation for the genus in tropical Asia, a large number of additional species were described from this region (J. Polhemus, 1989; Chen &amp; Nieser, 1991; D. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC6BEB4F509FFF5FC07FEDAFB54FE71" author="Polhemus, D" box="[1017,1193,382,406]" pageId="16" pageNumber="681" pagination="74 - 78" refId="ref18915" refString="Polhemus, D. A., 1994. A new species of Aphelocheirus from Sumatra, and addenda to the world checklist. Journal of the New York Entomological Society, 102: 74 - 78." type="journal article" year="1994">Polhemus, 1994</bibRefCitation>
; Liu &amp; Zheng, 1994; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC6BEB4F509FFF5FA70FEDAFC3EFE51" author="Sites, R" pageId="16" pageNumber="681" pagination="127 - 134" refId="ref19397" refString="Sites, R. W., B. J. Nichols &amp; S. Permkam, 1997. The Naucoridae (Heteroptera) of southern Thailand. The Pan-Pacific Entomologist, 73: 127 - 134." type="journal article" year="1997">Sites et al., 1997</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC6BEB4F509FFF5FC2FFE3AFBAAFE51" author="Zettel, H" box="[977,1111,414,438]" pageId="16" pageNumber="681" pagination="77 - 97" refId="ref19915" refString="Zettel, H., 1998. Neue Taxa der Gattung Aphelocheirus Westwood, 1833 (Insecta: Heteroptera: Aphelocheiridae) aus der Orientalischen Region sowie Bemerkungen zu einigen beschriebenen Arten und zu den Raubbeinen der Naucoroidea. Annalen des Naturhistorischen Museums in Wien, 100 B: 77 - 97." type="journal article" year="1998">Zettel, 1998</bibRefCitation>
, 1999, 2000, 2001; Nieser et al., 2004; Sites, 2005; Sites &amp; Zettel, 2005; Zettel &amp; Papáček, 2006; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC6BEB4F509FFF5FC7BFE7AFBC2FE11" author="Liu, G" box="[901,1087,478,502]" pageId="16" pageNumber="681" pagination="272 - 276" refId="ref18409" refString="Liu, G. - Q. &amp; J. - H. Ding, 2005. A new species and two new records of the genus Aphelocheirus (Hemiptera: Aphelocheiridae) from China. Entomotaxonomia, 27: 272 - 276. (Text in Chinese with English summary)." type="journal article" year="2005">Liu &amp; Ding, 2005</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC6BEB4F509FFF5FBB6FE7AFB02FE11" author="Thirumalai, G" box="[1096,1279,478,502]" pageId="16" pageNumber="681" pagination="55 - 61" refId="ref19756" refString="Thirumalai, G., 2008. Aphelocheirus (Aphelocheirus) narmadaensis sp. nov. (Hemiptera: Nepomorpha: Aphelocheiridae) from Madhya Pradesh, India. Zootaxa, 1923: 55 - 61." type="journal article" year="2008">Thirumalai, 2008</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC6BEB4F509FFF5FAF6FE7AFA43FE11" author="Zettel, H" box="[1288,1470,478,502]" pageId="16" pageNumber="681" pagination="61 - 68" refId="ref20315" refString="Zettel, H., D. J. W. Lane &amp; S. Moore, 2008. Aphelocheirus (s. str.) bruneiensis sp. n., a new benthic water bug (Hemiptera: Heteroptera: Aphelocheiridae) from Brunei, and a key to Bornean Aphelocheirus. Zootaxa, 1920: 61 - 68." type="journal article" year="2008">Zettel et al., 2008</bibRefCitation>
; Zettel &amp; Tran, 2009; Zettel &amp; Pangantihon, 2010). As a result, the genus currently contains 92 species worldwide (exclusive of subspecies), with the vast majority of the species added since 1989 having come from tropical Asia. This rush of new taxonomic work was not accompanied by any synthetic review or supplementary monograph, leading to a rather confusing situation for non-specialists at the present time.
</paragraph>
